            reviewDate: 'December 16, 2023',
            semester: 'fall 2023',
            review: "This is my first course in the program, and I would say this course falls under easy to moderate scale for me. Initially I spent lot of time with the course, but once I got hang of what I am expected I found it manageable.  This course includes lot of writing, peer feedback every week for participation points. I would recommend this course to anyone who is comfortable with writing an atmost of 8 page assignment each week. Apart from 10 assignment and 2 tests( both are open book), this course has 1 individual project and 1 team project. I really enjoyed the lectures, the course is well structured and ed discussion was super friendly, TA's and fellow students helped a lot when it came to assignment clarification and other queries.",
