            reviewDate: 'December 9, 2023',
            semester: 'fall 2023',
            review: "This was my 8th class in OMSCS, and it was by far my least favorite class. After reading all the positive reviews from the previous semesters, I felt like I got duped into taking this class.\nThis class goes at the speed of a summer class, but it's full semester length. Look at the summer class schedule, it follows the same cadence as normal semesters.\nThe amount of unnecessary busywork in this class is infuriating. Writing one 6-8 page paper each week is alright, but you need to peer review 3 papers by Thursday, complete peer surveys, watch a few hours of lecture, and read 30-50 pages of dense whitepapers (I did not) each week. Oh and also new for this semester is an extra 12 page paper you are supposed to be working on while completing your weekly 6-8 page papers.\nLike all the other students echoed on here, the exams are NOT a 30 question multiple choice, they are 150 question T/Fs where the questions are purposely worded to be un-Ctrl-F able. Another wonderful thing is you don't get a week off for the midterm, meaning you have to write a weekly paper + take the midterm + everything else for that week.\nThe group project is a 30+ (including appendix) page paper that is literally the exact same thing as our weekly papers. Which is also pretty similar to what we did in the extra 12 pager. So we basically walked through the same process 3 times in a row, which felt like a waste of time.\nI seriously don't recommend taking this class. If you joined OMSCS because you love programming/software, seriously do not take this class. It doesn't matter if you can handle the weekly papers, all the other extraneous garbage will wear away any enthusiasm until you wish you took any other elective.",
