            review: "The lectures are great, and Dr. Joyner did a good job creating this class, but seriously DO NOT take this if you're not interested in HCI. My lack of interest in the topic made this course a slog. I just needed an easy class to take with AOS (and I saw all the great reviews). I ended up hating it as a result. This class has so much busywork; you need to write 7+ page papers every week, and the final project is a 20 page paper. On top of that, part of your grade is participation, so you have to do peer reviews (you need to do 6 a week if you want to actually get your participation points, which means reading 48 pages of other students' writing), answer surveys (arguably the easiest one), or talk on EdStem (I never had a single question I needed to ask, and I'm not going to sit at my computer and monitor EdStem so I can be the first to answer a question). You can't even skim the readings (20+ pages a week) because the exams ask you about what the author would have thought about a statement, not what is in the paper. I don't think I took notes on a single lecture and I'll probably still end up with an A, but I dreaded doing the assignments each week. I don't know if I learned anything from this class other than how to write a paper in 2-3 hours.",
            rating: 1,
