            reviewDate: 'May 2, 2019',
            semester: 'spring 2019',
            review: "Pros:\n\nVery high quality materials and course design.\nConstant load, in the main part.\nVery clear hand-holding criteria for grading.\nIntellectually non-demanding.\nStudents retain CITI certificates.\nDoing PeerFeedback properly helps learn a ton.\nCould be paired with other courses.\nInstructor and TAs are very active on Piazza.\nTests are open-everything.\nEasy workload after the start of group project (with a good team).\n\nCons:\n\nBusy work, constantly high, but not demanding workload. Regular week: PeerFeedback (2 hours), Videos (3 hours), Required Readings (6 hours), Execute ahead some survey/interview (4 hours), Assignment (8 hours), prep for test or do project (8 hours, unlimited).\nHuge spikes in workload when tests, assignments and projects overlap (4 times a semester).\nGroup project, aka lottery.\nA LOT of required readings, which is impossible to thoroughly read through.\nNo one is doing PeerFeedback by the end.\nParticipation credit in general is a joke.\nTests are hard. 1+ sd above average is just below 90%.\nGrading on assignments and projects is too generous and non-challenging.\nNo coding at all.\nHuge amount of writing: 10 assignments 8+ pages each, 2 projects 30+ (more like 50) pages each.\n\nTips:\n\nStart CITI, Projects beforehand. Ideally ASAP.\nPrepare for tests beforehand.\nTake notes on readings and videos. Could easily take you into 50+ hours/week. Only do glossary for quick search during the test of where term is coming from.\nDon't read and don't skim readings. Stay in the middle.\nFollow prompts literally for an easy 100% on assignments and projects.\nAvoid appendices on assignments and projects.\nDo not overdo on assignments and projects. Don't dive too deep to save time.\nChoose teammates early on Piazza, don't wait for survey to come out.\nSplit the load on group project, avoid working together on something. Waste of effort.\nTests are very tricky, look for literal quote.\nTest 1 is difficult on videos, Test 2 is difficult on readings.\nUpload coarse assignment early to secure at least some grade.\nReferences are not important. Don't quote and don't reference. Saves time.\nPreload as much as possible.\n",
